lungen und Erkenntnisse der Medientheorie und -geschichte machen den Band zur Pflichtlektüre für Lehramtsstudierende, Referendar_innen und Lehrer_innen unterschiedlicher Fachrichtungen.  aNowadays, media determine the daily routine of schools. But what are media? How has media been fought about over the centuries? This volume offers the foundations for a qualified confrontation with questions of media reflection and the use of media in school praxis. A historical overview shows the structures of the debates around the possibilities and dangers of the use of media, and thus serves to make the debate more objective. The comprehensible and competent representation of the central concepts, developments and discoveries of media theory make this book essential reading for students in education and student teachers from diverse subject areas.  afunded by OGeSoMo  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGeneral education. 4aBildung. 4aEinführung. 4aHandbuch. 4aMedienerziehung. 4aMedienpädagogik. 4aMedienreflexion. 4aMedientheorie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aPädagogik. 4aSchule. 7aEDUCATION / Research.2bisacsh  aEducation.  aHandbook.  aIntroduction.  aMedia Education.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia Theory.  aPedagogy.  aReflection of the Media.  aSchool.1 aLeskau, Linda.1 aLohse, Kathrin.1 aMalmsheimer, Arne.1 aSchröter, Jens.1 aSchwering, Gregor, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut2 aOGeSoMoefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2017 Part 2z978311076666008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus e